  "prompt": "How does this coffee machine work?",
  "response": "Coffee machines can vary widely in design and function, but I\u2019ll give you a general overview of how most standard drip coffee machines work. If you're referring to a specific type (e.g., espresso machine, French press, pod-based machine), let me know!\n\n### Basic Drip Coffee Machine Workflow:\n1. **Water Reservoir**:  \n   You fill the reservoir with cold water. The amount of water determines how much coffee the machine will make.\n\n2. **Heating Element**:  \n   The machine heats the water to an optimal brewing temperature (usually between 195\u00b0F and 205\u00b0F / 90\u00b0C to 96\u00b0C).  \n\n3. **Brew Basket**:  \n   Ground coffee is placed in a filter inside the brew basket. The filter can be paper (disposable) or reusable (metal or mesh).\n\n4. **Brewing Process**:  \n   - The heated water is pumped or dripped onto the coffee grounds.  \n   - As the water passes through the grounds, it extracts the coffee\u2019s flavors, oils, and caffeine.  \n   - The brewed coffee drips into the carafe below.  \n\n5. **Carafe**:  \n   The carafe collects the brewed coffee. It\u2019s usually made of glass or thermal material to keep the coffee warm. Some machines have a warming plate underneath to maintain the temperature.\n\n6. **Controls**:  \n   Most machines have buttons or dials to start brewing, adjust the brew strength, or set a timer for automatic brewing.\n\n### Main Components:\n- **Water Reservoir**: Holds the water.  \n- **Heating Element**: Heats the water.  \n- **Showerhead**: Distributes water evenly over the coffee grounds.  \n- **Filter Basket**: Holds the coffee grounds and filter.  \n- **Carafe**: Collects the brewed coffee.  \n- **Control Panel**: Manages settings like brew time, strength, and on/off.\n\nIf you\u2019re using a different type of coffee machine (e.g., espresso machine, French press, or single-serve pod machine), the process will differ. Let me know if you\u2019d like details on a specific type!",
